Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a
large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate
the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the chicken has browned, stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and
@chipotle paste{20%g} (use less if you don't like heat).

Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and
@water{100%ml} for the chicken (see ingredients for amount).

Bring the chicken filling to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

> TIP: Continue cooking for a little longer if the sauce needs to thicken more,
> or add a splash of water to loosen.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} on a #cutting board{} (2 per person), spoon the
filling down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little @oil{drizzle} over the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{}, then lay
in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath
so they don't unroll. Top with the grated cheese.

Bake the enchiladas on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When ready, share the enchiladas between your plates and serve with the wedges
alongside. Finish with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} on top. Enjoy!